[NPC] Nyshyn: Ah, from Lori.
[NPC] Nyshyn: Doubtless you are going back to see her to collect your fee.
[NPC] Nyshyn: Since I have a letter I hope to get to her soon, would you mind delivering it to her?
[NPC Internal] Sure, I'll do it.
[NPC] Nyshyn: Most pleasing, and thank you.
[NPC Narrate] -Nyshyn smiles as she gives you the letter and six Octa.-
[NPC] Nyshyn: This letter should also serve as proof that you did deliver the box to me; she'll appreciate that.
[NPC] Nyshyn: The Octas are for you to keep, for ensuring speedy delivery.
[NPC] Nyshyn: Take care, and may your path be lit, Sir.

[To] Lori Tryllyn

[NPC Internal] I have a letter for you.
[NPC] Lori: Oh, she had a letter for me, eh?
[NPC Narrate] -Lori scans the message, frowning.-
[NPC] Lori: Hmm.
[NPC] Lori: Could I ask you to do just one more favor for me?
[NPC] Lori: I just need you to peek at something in the plaza, it wouldn't take long.
[NPC Internal] Ok, I'll go.
[NPC] Lori: Fantastic.
[NPC] Lori: You're so helpful.
[NPC] Lori: So, you know those big stone blocks around the statue of the Masked God?
[NPC] Lori: There are numbers on some of them.
[NPC] Lori: I need to know what the number is on the one closest to Harnquist's smithy.
[NPC] Lori: I think it's five hundred something, but I don't remember the exact figure.
[NPC] Lori: Please be sure you get the right one.
[NPC Internal] 550
[NPC] Lori: Ah, yes, that was it.
[NPC] Lori: Thank you.
[NPC Narrate] -Lori studies the letter again, reading it very slowly, her eyebrows quirking upward now and then.-
[NPC] Lori: Interesting…
[NPC] Lori: I wonder…
[NPC] Lori: no, he wouldn't…
[NPC Narrate] -Lori re-reads a portion of the letter.-
[NPC] Lori: Or would he..?
[NPC] Lori: Hmm!
[NPC] Lori: We'll have to meet and talk.
[NPC Narrate] -Lori looks up at you.-
[NPC] Lori: Oh, your fee, sorry to keep you waiting.
[NPC] Lori: Thank you for your help today.
[NPC Narrate] -Lori opens her purse, takes out some coins, considers, takes out a few more, and passes them to you.-
[NPC] Lori: Come back and see me some time, I may have something else you can help me with, and there's more coin to be had where those came from.
[NPC Narrate] -Lori winks.-
[NPC] Lori: Take care, my good Sir.

